sentences: The vocals were announced to have been dropped in favor of Vocaloid 3 productions on December 1, 2011.
On March 19, 2015, a new version of Luka developed for Vocaloid 4, called Megurine Luka V4X, was released containing a package of 6 vocals - 4 for Japanese and 2 for English.
In 2010, Luka was ranked as the 3rd most popular Vocaloid product Crypton has sold.
In October 2013, Luka's Vocaloid 2 software disappeared off the top 10 products charts as the Hatsune Miku V3 and its bundle package disrupted the chart rankings.
Luka had already fallen to 6th place during the 2013 period as a result of the KAITO V3 release, but this was the first time Luka had disappeared from the charts.
However, Vocaloid 2 vocals were mostly absent from the rankings in April 2014.
In March 2015, the Megurine Luka V4x package got the no.1 spot for the sales of all digital instruments on Big Fish Audio.
Megurine Luka (巡音ルカ) is a persona voiced by a singing synthesizer application developed by Crypton Future Media, headquartered in Sapporo, Japan.
Luka was developed by Crypton Future Media using Yamaha's Vocaloid 2.

After the charts began to settle down again, Luka began to occupy the same spot on the charts that the Vocaloid 1 KAITO package previously occupied (6th-8th place), putting the popularity of the product on par with the older product.
By mid-2014, both she and the Vocaloid 2 Kagamine Rin\Len package no longer held constant places in the rankings and were constantly on and off Crypton Future Media sales charts.
Her dress was designed to look old fashioned, to make her represent the past, as a form of contrast, the "∞" on her neck area represents "sound around".
